<%= render layout: "shared/information_dialog", :locals => {id: "information-dialog-search", title: "How to use Search", wide: true} do %>
  <%= javascript_tag "var showHideTexts = ['Show syntax examples', 'Hide syntax examples'];" %>
  The feature has two uses: Searching (database) and Filtering (local results). <br/><br/>

  <span class="font-bold">Searching</span><br/>
  Overall Search can be used to find any column (global) matches.
  Column search is used to find matches in the respective column(s).
  Search boxes are marked with the <span class="icon-cloud"></span> icon. <br/>
  Search syntax comprises of:
  <ul>
    <li><span class="font-regular">x AND y</span> (Intersection) results with both x and y present.</li>
    <li><span class="font-regular">x OR y</span> (Union) results with either x or y present.</li>
    <li><span class="font-regular">y â€”x</span> (Exclusion) results with y, but not x present.</li>
    <li><span class="font-regular">"x y z"</span> (Exact match) results containing the phrase 'x y z', in that order. Case sensitive.</li>
    <li><span class="font-regular">x y</span> (Exact match) same as "x y". Default.</li>
  </ul>
  This syntax cannot be used for searching tags. Tags are found with the ; separator (e.g. SEND; SDTM) <br/>

  <%= render layout: "shared/show_more", :locals => {:size => "tiny", show_text: "Show syntax examples"} do %>
    Valid examples:
    <ul>
      <li>Fred AND Harry</li>
      <li>Fred AND Harry -Oliver</li>
      <li>Fred OR Harry</li>
      <li>Fred OR Harry -Oliver</li>
      <li>"Fred Harry Oliver"</li>
      <li>Fred Harry Oliver (same as "Fred Harry Oliver")</li>
    </ul>
    Invalid examples:
    <ul>
      <li>Fred - Harry</li>
      <li>-Harry</li>
      <li>Fred AND Harry Oliver</li>
      <li>Fred OR "Harry Oliver"</li>
      <li>Fred AND Harry OR Oliver</li>
    </ul>
  <% end %>
  <br/>
  As some searches may take longer, the results are fetched in batches. New searches cannot be conducted while a search is active. To stop an on-going search, click the <span class="text-accent-2">Abort</span> button.<br/><br/>

  <span class="font-bold">Filtering</span><br/>
  Local filtering is used to narrow down local results retrieved by Search.
  Overall filter will match input from all columns (top-right Filter field), while column filters are limited to their respective column data. <br/>
  Search syntax cannot be used for filters. <br/><br/>

  Multiple Search and Filter fields can be combined to narrow the results.
<% end %>
